revision.text:
'''Enterprise Value Tax''' was a tax proposal considered by the [[United States Congress]].<ref>Moody, J. Scott. [https://www.washingtonpolicy.org/publications/notes/economic-impact-enterprise-value-tax "The Economic Impact of an Enterprise Value Tax"] [[Washington Policy Center]] (November 2011)</ref> It passed in the [[US House of Representatives]] in 2010 as part of "H.R. 4213: American Jobs and Closing Tax Loopholes Act". The bill was not passed by the [[US Senate|Senate]], and hence did not become law. Nonetheless the concept of the tax has recurred in succeeding years,{{citation needed|date=October 2015}} most recently as a speculation over [[Donald Trump]]'s promise to do "something huge".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.city-journal.org/2015/eon0922ca.html|title=Getting Away With Murder by Clifford S. Asness, City Journal September 22, 2015|work=city-journal.org}}</ref>
The tax was opposed as detrimental to entrepreneurs re-investing funds from the sale of businesses. It was described by [[Richard A. Baker (businessman)|Richard A. Baker]], CEO of the [[Hudson's Bay Company]], as "a stealth attack on capital gains".<ref>Baker, Richard A. [https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052748704009804575308981778779248 "A Stealth Attack on Capital Gains"] ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'' (June 17, 2010)</ref> Conversely the "[[carried interest]] tax loophole" was cited as reason to increase taxes on those doing well from the taxation of certain businesses, notably hedge fund managers.<ref>Delevingne, Lawrence. [https://www.cnbc.com/2015/05/22/hedge-fund-managers-stung-by-class-warfare-rhetoric.html "Hedge fund managers stung by 'class warfare' rhetoric"] [[CNBC]] (May 22, 2015)</ref>
[[Enterprise value]], in this context, has been described as another expression for [[goodwill (accounting)|goodwill]].<ref>Judge, Steve. [http://www.pegcc.org/issues/comment-letters/pegcc-carried-interest-submission-to-senate-finance-committee-individual-income-tax-working-group/ "PEGCC Carried Interest Submission to Senate Finance Committee Individual Income Tax Working Group"] [[Private Equity Growth Capital Council]] (April 15, 2015)</ref>
