Founded in 1990, '''Meritas''' is a [[Professional services networks|professional services network]] consisting of a [[Law firm network|global alliance]] of [[business law]] firms formerly known as '''Commercial Law Affiliates'''.<ref name="ccw">{{cite news|last=Wright|first=Karen|date=April 18, 2007|title=Focus: Law Firm Associations|work=Corporate Counsel Weekly|publisher=[[Bureau of National Affairs]]}}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=Firms find benefit in law firm networks |publisher=Minnesota Lawyer |date=Mar 17, 2008}}</ref> In 2018, the association's membership included over 180 law firms in 90 countries, with more than 7600 lawyers worldwide.<ref>{{cite news|title=Alliance extends reach of regional firms: Meritas tax group even works jointly on files|url=http://www.financialpost.com/story-printer.html?id=96f40304-b6a1-4b35-95b7-a4d772dd82ad|date=April 9, 2008|first= Jim|last=Middlemiss|accessdate= November 14, 2009|work=[[Financial Post]]}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> Meritas is a non-profit corporation headquartered in [[Minneapolis]], [[Minnesota]]. Membership is extended by invitation only, and regular recertification by all firms every three years is a requirement of membership.<ref name="calawyer" /> There is a staff of about 15 who handle the organization's administration and review referrals to ensure that the organization's standards are maintained.<ref name=Int>{{citation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tDUis4t-j74C |page=334 |title=The internationalization of the practice of law |author=Jens I. Drolshammer, Michael Pfeifer}}</ref>
==Membership==
Jennifer McPhee, writing for ''Canadian Lawyer'', described Meritas as one of the "more established by-invitation only legal networks that do extensive research before carefully selecting one firm per jurisdiction."<ref name="calawyer">{{cite web |url=http://www.mggg.com/publications/2007/p2007_02_07_cdnlawyer1.pdf |title=Report on Law Associations: Going Global |first=Jennifer |last=McPhee |date=February 2007 |work=Canadian Lawyer |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714082357/http://www.mggg.com/publications/2007/p2007_02_07_cdnlawyer1.pdf |archivedate=July 14, 2011 |accessdate=November 14, 2009 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> ''Corporate Counsel Weekly'' also wrote, "Meritas determines significant business or economic centers where member firms' clients may need local counsel in order to determine where it will have its members,"<ref name="ccw" /> and that "...all member firms provide Meritas with quarterly referral reports, listing all Meritas-originated referrals made to and from the firm for the stated period and cooperate in evaluating specific matters."<ref name="ccw" /> If a firm does not receive good marks, its membership with the organization may be terminated.<ref>{{cite news|last=Tromans|first=R.|date=October 2007|title=Alternative hits the mainstream|work=European Lawyer|page=30}}</ref>
