'''Religious police''' is the [[police force]] responsible for the enforcement of [[form (religion)|religious norms]] and associated [[religious law]]s.
While most police enforcing religious norms in the modern world are [[Islamic religious police|Islamic]] and found in Muslim countries such as [[Committee for the Promotion of Virtue and the Prevention of Vice (Saudi Arabia)|Saudi Arabia]] or [[Basij|Iran]], some are not (for example in Vietnam, the religious security police monitor “extremist” religious groups, detaining and interrogating suspected Dega Protestants or Ha Mon Catholics).<ref>{{cite web|author= Angelina Theodorou |url=http://www.pewresearch.org/fact-tank/2014/03/19/religious-police-found-in-nearly-one-in-ten-countries-worldwide/ |title=Religious police found in one-in-ten countries worldwide |publisher=[[Pew Research Center]]|date=2014-03-19 |accessdate=2014-03-24}}</ref>
