{{Orphan|date=April 2017}}

'''Stephen R. Perry''' (born 1950) is a [[Canadian]] scholar in the fields of [[jurisprudence]] and [[political philosophy]]. He is the John J. O'Brien Professor of [[Law]] and Professor of [[Philosophy]] at the [[University of Pennsylvania]]. From 2003 to 2005, he was the Fiorello La Guardia Professor of Law and Professor of Philosophy at [[NYU Law School]].

==Education and career==

Perry earned his law degree at the [[University of Toronto]] and his D.Phil at [[Oxford University]] under the direction of [[Ronald Dworkin]].<ref>https://www.law.upenn.edu/cf/faculty/sperry/</ref>  He taught for nearly a decade at [[McGill University]] prior to moving to Penn in 1996.

